  <h2>The Deal: A Fully Managed Sportsbook</h2>

  <p>DigiPlus Interactive Corp. (PSE: PLUS), the publicly listed operator behind the Philippines' leading online gaming platform ArenaPlus, has confirmed the selection of Malta-based sportsbook technology supplier Altenar to power its sports betting operations. The partnership will see ArenaPlus migrate its sportsbook entirely to Altenar's fully managed platform, a turnkey solution that encompasses odds compilation, trading, risk management, localization, in-play betting, and regulatory compliance infrastructure.</p>

  <p>The deal was announced jointly by Dinos Stranomitis, Chief Operating Officer of Altenar, and Erick Su, Head of ArenaPlus, during a press briefing held in Makati City. The partnership marks Altenar's first major deployment in Southeast Asia and DigiPlus's most significant technology investment in its sportsbook vertical since launching ArenaPlus.</p>

  <p>"The Philippine market is unlike any other in Asia," Stranomitis said. "The combination of a PAGCOR-regulated framework, a sports-obsessed population, and a mobile-first user base creates an enormous opportunity for a localized, data-driven sportsbook. We designed the ArenaPlus deployment specifically for this market."</p>

  <h2>PBA Player Props: The Localization Bet</h2>

  <p>Perhaps the most significant product innovation in the Altenar-ArenaPlus partnership is the introduction of a comprehensive player proposition bets portfolio for Philippine Basketball Association (PBA) games. The PBA is the country's most-watched and most-wagered domestic sporting league, with a passionate fan base that extends from Metro Manila to the provinces. Yet until now, PBA player props have been largely absent from licensed Philippine sportsbooks, a gap that Altenar and ArenaPlus are now positioning to fill.</p>

  <p>Altenar's in-house statistical modeling team has built PBA-specific models that generate pre-match and in-play player prop markets, including points, rebounds, assists, and combined stat lines for individual PBA players. The models draw on historical PBA data, injury reports, and real-time game state information.</p>

  <div class="pull-quote">
    <p>"The Philippine market is unlike any other in Asia. The combination of a PAGCOR-regulated framework, a sports-obsessed population, and a mobile-first user base creates an enormous opportunity."</p>
    <cite>Dinos Stranomitis, COO, Altenar</cite>
  </div>

  <h2>Sportradar Integrity Integration</h2>

  <p>The ArenaPlus platform will integrate Sportradar's Integrity Exchange, a monitoring system that detects suspicious betting patterns in real time across global sportsbook networks. The integration is designed to address match-fixing concerns, which have periodically surfaced in Philippine sports, particularly in lower-tier basketball and football leagues.</p>

  <p>Sportradar's system works by comparing betting patterns on ArenaPlus against aggregated data from hundreds of sportsbooks worldwide. Anomalies trigger alerts that are reviewed by both Sportradar's integrity team and ArenaPlus's compliance department, with escalation to PAGCOR when warranted.</p>

  <p>Erick Su emphasized the integrity angle during the press briefing: "We want ArenaPlus to be the most trusted sportsbook in the Philippines. Sportradar integration is not a marketing gimmick. It's a foundational requirement for long-term credibility with both regulators and players."</p>

